<apex:page tabStyle="Message__c" showHeader="false" standardStylesheets="true">
    
    <style>
        body {background: url('{!URLFOR("/img/in-page_clouds.png")}') top left no-repeat;}
    </style>
    <apex:form >
        <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail" title="Introducing Messages">
            <apex:pageBlockSection columns="2" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>Messages represent real-world events. These occur all the time, for example, a clock strikes midnight, or a bank account becomes empty, etc.</p>
                    <p>A Message captures this data into a common structure that can be handed to different Processes to act on.</p>
                    <p>All Messages enter a queue, which can be seen from the Messages tab.</p>
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <apex:image width="360" value="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Message/messageProcessFunnel.png')}" />
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
            
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="List View Buttons:" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Message/pauseQueue.png')}" /> halts the processing of new Messages. New Messages will be Queued up outside of their destined Sequence. Old Messages already in a Sequence will filter through to completion.</p>
                    <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Message/resumeQueue.png')}" /> resumes the processing of all Messages.</p>
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
            
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Detail Page Buttons:" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Message/processMessage.png')}" /> forces this Message to be Processed immediately. You can use this to process individual Messages when the system is paused, or to reprocess any Message that could not be processed.</p>
                    <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Message/showData.png')}" /> takes you to the native view of the related data pointed to by the Message. This could be used to edit or audit the data that any Message hands into a given Process.</p>
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
            
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Click [Continue] to proceed." columns="1" collapsible="false" />
        </apex:pageBlock>
    </apex:form>
</apex:page>